               <t:note>
                  <t:date type="foundation" notBefore="1300" notAfter="1400">1300-1400</t:date>
                  <t:desc type="foundation">Local tradition tells that the founder was <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS12533Taklom">Taḵlom</t:persName>, hence the name of the church; the local people are thus daqqi Taḵlom, i.e. his descendants.</t:desc>
                  <t:ab type="history">Gadām. 
It is considered a monastic community, but currently there are no monks. Local tradition speaks of "one thousand monks" who once resided around.
At the foot of the mountain, there are collapsed structures of a rock-hewn church (?); some caves at the place of ascension to the church appear to be an old church or monks dwelling; a few other caverns in the rock on the other side are were used as burial places.
</t:ab>
